<subSubSection pageId="45" pageNumber="82" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="45" pageNumber="82">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="45" pageNumber="82">-Wings are usually about same length in both sexes; when folded, tips of tegmina vary from falling short of the tip of the abdomen to more or less level with, or even surpassing, the hind knees. Coloration variable; bright and contrasting in some, with face and medial stripe on occiput dark and pale spots on upper face of hind femur. In others, paler, particularly on the face and with uniformly pale rusty-brown upper and outer face of hind femur, without notable maculation.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
